                                       <div class="fusion-text fusion-text-1 fusion-text-no-margin" style="margin-top:-50px;">
                                       <p>The digital access tracker is a tool that allows companies to monitor their accessibility standards and receive feedback on how to improve them. With this tool, businesses can fill out audits based on their venues, such as restaurants, stores, or offices, and receive insights on how well they are doing in terms of accessibility for people with disabilities. The tracker will evaluate factors such as the availability of wheelchair ramps, the clarity of signage, or the presence of audio descriptions for visually impaired customers. By using this technology, companies can identify areas for improvement and ensure that they are providing a welcoming and inclusive environment for all customers.</p>
